metadata.name: La Veranada #10
metadata.description:
My mother lives in the countryside with her husband and her work is the breeding and grazing of goats, cows and horses. They live a cyclical life marked by two big stages during their livestock year: "La Veranada" and "La Invernada".
The "invernada" is the place where they live during what we could call the long winter, that is, from April to November. "La Invernada" is below, in the plains, in the pampas, in accessible places, where it is easy to supply the animals with fodder.
"La Veranada" is the place where they go during the long summer, from November to April, it is above, in the mountain ranges, on the heights, where the summer pastures abound, where they go for months to take care, alone, of the goats, cows and calves.
The transfer of the animals to the summer pasture is called "Arreo", my mother's husband guides the animals on his horse. The "Arreo" lasts about 5 days.
In both places they live in what they call "el puesto". "El puesto" is their home.
In "La veranada", "El puesto" is simple. A common living room, with a wood stove, a table, some chairs and shelves to store flour, *"mate" and salt. A small bedroom replenishes the strength worn out by the daily work. Water for drinking, cooking and washing is drawn from a nearby stream.
Work is abundant. As a common element, both in winter and summer, my mother's husband rides a horse daily and, accompanied by his dogs, goes to "watch" the cattle.
As a final point I wanted to thank you for taking your time and reading the story behind this project that I really enjoyed doing it, and on my tw profile you can read this story with real photos.

*Mate: is an Argentinean infusion, which is present all day long in the life of people who live in the countryside. It give you energy.

Press "S" in live mode to save image 2600 x 3000.
Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run.
Created by Fernando. NFT License 2.0.

metadata.description: The world without a mother without a woman is an empty world. But this material is delicate like glass, fragile, sensitive and transparent. We must be careful in our behavior towards it.

metadata.name: Lineas #133
metadata.description:
Búscame entre mis letras por que en ellas siempre voy a estar
y en los versos de mis poemas mi corazón escucharás...

Lee cada palabra que encuentres donde quieres buscar
esas que ya conoces y que además te hacen extrañar.
Si te emocionan sueña siempre con algo más, no llores
por que existe un camino donde las letras tienen su punto y final.

El amor es un poema o un milagro terrenal, es la magia
que nos envuelve a los que nos podemos enamorar.
Amar cuesta y cuando se ama duele, se sufre, se llora
por el ser amado, eso es lo que tu alma atesora.

Cada verso que escribo lleva en su contenido un significado,
una promesa, un abrazo entre líneas y un beso de enamorado...

AMOR ENTRE LÍNEAS.
poema de De Lorenzo Román.

-----

Press 'e' to export a 1640 x 2000 pixels PNG

Press 'h' to export a 3280 x 4000 pixels PNG

-----



Artwork by @cristianrohr 2022.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1292
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Patched with Tartan #1
metadata.description:
Patched with Tartan is a generative patchwork made with p5.js. 
Evolving from my earlier work, "Patched", this new piece has 576 possible layout combinations, 17 new printed patterns on a choice of 7 new textile textures and two new woven fabrics with near infinite colour variation chosen from one of 13 palettes. 

This piece introduces a new tartan fabric which gives it its name. Due to the vagaries of generative art it is quite possible that a piece won't contain any tartan though so all holders of Patched with Tartan will receive free access to a brand new pure tartan token in a couple of weeks.

'2' to regenerate at 2000x2000
'3' to regenerate at 3000x3000
'r' to regenerate at window size

metadata.description:
This artwork is a piece of pure tartan cloth, developed as one possible fabric for the project Patched with Tartan, expanded on a little and offered freely to holders of that project because I love it.

'2' to render at 2000 x 2000
'3' to render at 3000 x 3000
'w' to render square at min of screen width or height

metadata.name: DisOrder #399
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

metadata.name: Origin Undecided #1
metadata.description:
These feel like communications from an unknown place.

Ultimately, this is a deeper exploration of familiar concepts. The code generates patterns for a couple million lines, each with extremely low opacity. As they're drawn and overlap, the color accumulates and shapes begin to form.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Balanced #105
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced
